# class (or style) inside a cond-attr branch on a forwarding element is
# rejected: the root's class merge is emitted once at a static site and cannot
# account for a conditional contribution (it would emit a duplicate class
# attribute next to the merged one). The composable form expresses this.
-- input.gsx --
package views

component Box(active bool) {
	<div { if active { class="on" } } { attrs... }>x</div>
}
-- diagnostics.golden --
4:21: conditional class inside { if } on an element with attribute forwarding cannot join the class merge; use the composable form (class={ "on": active }) instead
